{"description":"App.AddProject() in internal/ui/app.go currently appends without checking for duplicates.

Issue: If bdb /path/to/foo is run multiple times, duplicate entries are added to the workspace.

Fix: Before appending, check if a project with the same Dir already exists in a.projects.

Current code (line 234):
func (a *App) AddProject(project domain.Project) {
    a.projects = append(a.projects, project)
}

Should be:
func (a *App) AddProject(project domain.Project) {
    for _, p := range a.projects {
        if p.Dir == project.Dir {
            return // Already exists
        }
    }
    a.projects = append(a.projects, project)
}"}

